    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.1649/0010-065x-74.4.897>
    bibo:endPage "921" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "The Coleopterists Bulletin" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2020-12-22" ;
    bibo:startPage "897" ;
    bibo:volume "74" ;
    dc:creator "Brunke, A. J.; Zmudzinska, A.; Buffam, J." ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "An Integrative Taxonomic Review of the Quedius erythrogaster Mannerheim Species Group in North America (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Quediini)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334522>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334530>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334548>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334526> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334522>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Habitus of erythrogaster species group members. A) Quedius bicoloris, B) Q. alesi, new species, C) Q. miltoni, new species, D) Q. pullmani, E) Q. praticola, new species, F) Q. compransor, G) Q. pinetis, new species. Arrows indicate abdominal segment VI. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5334522/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334530>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. A) Quedius compransor, hind margin of head, basal puncture close to nuchal ridge, B) Q. pinetis, new species, male abdominal sternites, arrow indicates setose patch of sternite VI, C) Q. compransor, distal antennomeres, D) Q. praticola, new species, distal antennomeres, E) Q. compransor, detail of pronotal microsculpture, F) Q. pinetis, new species, detail of pronotal microsculpture. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C–F = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5334530/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334548>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Distributions of erythrogaster species group. A) Quedius bicoloris, B) Q. erythrogaster (circles), Q. miltoni, new species (pink triangles), Q. alesi, new species (blue squares), C) Q. pullmani, D) Q. praticola, new species (pink triangles), Q. compransor (circles), Q. pinetis, new species (blue squares)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5334548/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5334526>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Fifty percent majority rule consensus tree from an unpartitioned Bayesian phylogenetic analysis of the “barcoding” region of COI. Posterior probability, SH-aLRT, and ultrafast bootstrap values, respectively, to the left of the corresponding node. Nodes colored as: green, PP ≥ 0.90, and either SH-aLRT ≥ 80 or UFB ≥ 95; yellow, one of PP ≥ 0.90, SH-aLRT ≥ 80, or UFB ≥ 95; red, PP <0.90, SH-aLRT <80, and UFB <95. Inset photo: Quedius alesi, new species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5334526/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

